"Served from a 12 oz. bottle. Pours a semi-opaque medium copper orange with an off white head. This beer leaves a decent amount of lacing as well.  Aroma is a rich blend of orange and other citrus along with very subtle pine notes without being cloying or overpowering. Taste is outstanding with a continuance of orangey citrus notes and pine plus with a barely detectable presence in the background that brings to mind children's aspirin believe it or not. Mouthfeel is full and smooth with just the right amount of carbonation. Overall this is an outstanding beer. Though I have some philosophical objections to to the arch-hipsterishness of Three Floyds in general, this might be the premier example of what an American pale ale should be."
